<emphasis id="DE81EAB3FFD2571DFF6BF8D5C335F8D0" bold="true" box="[151,286,1851,1876]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after our friend André Bertounesque (
<number id="5A3D2486FFD2571DFC0EF8D5C65DF8D0" box="[1010,1142,1851,1876]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" value="1971.0" valueMax="2005.0" valueMin="1937.0">
<date id="984B1061FFD2571DFC0EF8D5C65DF8D0" box="[1010,1142,1851,1876]" pageId="0" pageNumber="289" value="1937" valueMax="2005">1937–2005</date>
</number>
). André was a Canadian painter-artist known worldwide and was also an avid collector of spectacular and exotic insects. His collection of birdwings butterflies and beetles is now housed at the Montreal Insectarium, Québec, 
<collectingCountry id="94E27631FFD2571DFBA5F86DC69AF818" box="[1113,1201,1923,1948]" name="Canada" pageId="0" pageNumber="289">Canada</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
